exert efforts to prepare the Property Cards and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards, respectively, starting with the current year’s acquisition and recent years’ acquisitions and aim for a yearly increase of coverage until all PPE items are covered;
consider the creation of a permanent positions in the GSO and accounting office to carry out regular functions, particularly the conduct of annual physical count and maintenance of property records;
strengthen the controls on the handling and recording procedures for the PPE by performing a periodic reconciliation of the records of the accounting and the property offices and actual inventory results;
attend trainings relative to LRAMM by the DILG, to be able to adopt and follow the procedures set forth therein and eventually comply with the requirements thereof on reporting as prescribed under COA Circular 2015-008; and
