We recommended that the Bids and Awards Committee, who has the responsibility for ensuring that the procuring entity abides by the standards set forth by RA 9184 and its IRR, strictly adhere with all provisions of law, rules and regulations pertaining to procurements to protect at all times the interest of the local government unit. 

We further recommended that:

 An Annual Procurement Plan (APP) for supplies and materials be prepared  in order to have basis in determining the quantity and quality of supplies and materials to be procured and ensure that procurements will be made in a manner beneficial to the financial interest of the local government unit;

The procedural guidelines under GPPB Resolution No. 09-2009 dated November 23, 2009 be observed in all procurements through shopping and small-value procurement to ensure that prices obtained are advantageous to the local government unit;

