We recommended that the: 

a) Local Chief Executive (i) prioritize the creation of an Emergency Response Team   and (ii) provide them the adequacy of technical competency and skills in responding to disaster;   

b) MDRRMO (i) prepare the comprehensive and long-term Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction Management Plan (MDRRMP), formulate and implement a comprehensive and integrated LDRRMP in accordance with the national, regional and provincial framework, and policies on disaster risk reduction in close coordination with the Local Development Council (LDC) with the participation of various constituents through their inputs; and (i) prepare the monthly report on the sources and utilization of the LDRMMF and facilitate monitoring of the accomplishment vis-à-vis targeted projects for effective and efficient utilization of the Fund. 

